  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6592 trading just 2 points above the GEX flip at 6590 in a PIN regime, dealers are currently long gamma and providing stabilizing flow. The massive +83.3B gamma wall at 6600 (8 points above spot) means dealers will aggressively sell into any rally attempt toward that level, while the -5.3B negative gamma pocket at 6560 provides a buying cushion on dips. Given the dense positive GEX structure from 6590-6610 and the recent -7.3% decline over 5 minutes, expect dealers to step in as buyers here to hedge their short delta from falling prices.\n\n**Bottom line:** Price should find support near current levels with limited upside to 6600.",
